ce:section.ce:para:
The emission spectra and afterglow emission spectra of samples (Fig. 9
                        ) show that X-NCD/BA exhibits blue fluorescence around 442 nm, and green phosphorescence around 542 nm. The emission spectra and afterglow emission peaks of samples are different, which demonstrates the process of afterglow is different with photoluminescence. Similarly, converting the peak positions of the emission spectra and the afterglow emission spectra of X-CDs/BA into energy plot give us the hint of the energy gap. The energy level structure diagrams of the samples have been drawn, as shown in Fig. 10
                        . The Δ EST values are almost identical, which are 0.43 eV, 0.47 eV, 0.46 eV, 0.44 eV and 0.43 eV respectively. This result indicates that the introduction of N atoms did not significant affect the energy gap of the five samples. However, the afterglow persistent luminescence time of the samples varies greatly, which once again proves that the reaction time of the precursor affects the afterglow characteristics of the X-NCD/BA.
